message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. Folic acid supplementation is important in preventing neural tube defects in the developing fetus. The neural tube arises from the ectoderm during embryonic development. Therefore, folic acid supplementation protects against defects in tissues derived from the ectoderm.
We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. Folic acid helps prevent neural tube defects in the developing embryo, which arises from the ectoderm during embryonic development.

We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. Folic acid supplementation is recommended for pregnant women to prevent neural tube defects in the developing fetus. The neural tube forms from the ectodermal cell layer, so the correct answer is (C).
